quared, plus y, plus 0 point 2 5, close parenthesis, minus 0 point 2 5, equals 22 point 5\"></span>. Second, add 2.25 and 0.25 to both sides of the equation: <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, x squared, minus 3 x, plus 2 point 2 5, close parenthesis, plus, open parenthesis, y squared, plus y, plus 0 point 2 5, close parenthesis, equals 25\"></span>. Since <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared, minus 3 x, plus 2 point 2 5, equals, open parenthesis, x minus 1 point 5, close parenthesis, squared\"></span>, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y squared, plus y, plus 0 point 2 5, equals, open parenthesis, y plus 0 point 5, close parenthesis, squared\"></span>, and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"25 equals 5 squared\"></span>, it follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, x minus 1 point 5, close parenthesis, squared, plus, open parenthesis, y plus 0 point 5, close parenthesis, squared, equals 5 squared\"></span>. Therefore, the radius of the circle is 5.<p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and may be the result of errors in manipulating the equation or of a misconception about the standard form of the equation of a circle in the <span class=\"italic\">xy</span>-plane.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"
